<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(A)

	The Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Extension Term Monthly Rent shall be payable in accordance with the provisions for the payment of Monthly Rent under Section&nbsp;4 of the Lease.&#160; Except as provided below and specifically provided elsewhere in the Lease, no abatement or other concession whatsoever shall apply to the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Extension Term Monthly Rent.&#160; The foregoing notwithstanding, Lessor agrees to abate and forgive First Extension Term Monthly Rent (and, if necessary to exhaust such abatement, Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Extension Term Monthly Rent) and Lessee&#146;s payments of its proportionate share of Operating Expenses, Operating Costs and Real Estate Taxes in an aggregate amount equal to Two Million Three Hundred Thirty-Two Thousand Nine Hundred Seventy and 73/100 Dollars ($2,332,970.73), which abatement is to be applied to the payments of First Extension Term Monthly Rent (and, if necessary to exhaust such abatement, Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Extension Term Monthly Rent) and Lessee&#146;s proportionate share of Operating Expenses, Operating Costs and Real Estate Taxes first coming due from and after January&nbsp;1, 2015, until such abatement is exhausted.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	If no default by Lessee then exists beyond any applicable notice and cure period and Lessee complies with the provisions of this Section, on November&nbsp;1, 2019, the amount of the Addendum No.&nbsp;4 Letter of Credit or cash security shall be reduced to One Hundred Fifty Thousand Dollars ($150,000.00).&#160; The security shall be reduced as follows: (A)&nbsp;if the security is in the form of cash, Lessor shall, within ten (10)&nbsp;business days following notice by Lessee to Lessor that Lessee is entitled to reduce the security pursuant to this Section, deliver to Lessee the amount by which the cash security is reduced, or (B)&nbsp;if the security is in the form of the Addendum No.&nbsp;4 Letter of Credit, Lessee shall deliver to Lessor a consent to an amendment to the Addendum No.&nbsp;4 Letter of Credit (which amendment must be reasonably acceptable to Lessor in all respects), reducing the amount of the Addendum No.&nbsp;4 Letter of Credit by the amount of the permitted reduction, and Lessor shall execute such consent and such other documents as are reasonably necessary to reduce the amount of the Addendum No.&nbsp;4 Letter of Credit in accordance with the terms hereof.&nbsp; If Lessee delivers to Lessor a consent to an amendment to the Addendum No.&nbsp;4 Letter of Credit in accordance with the terms hereof, Lessor shall, within ten (10)&nbsp;business days after delivery of such consent, either (1)&nbsp;provide its reasonable objections to such amendment or (2)&nbsp;execute such consent in accordance with the terms hereof.
</FONT>

	Lessee
</FONT>
	shall continue in possession of the Demised Premises (as reduced hereby) in its &#147;as is&#148; condition as of November&nbsp;1, 2015, subject to Lessor&#146;s obligations under the Lease, such as with respect to repair and maintenance of the Building and performing its obligations under the Lease with respect to legal compliance.&#160; Lessee shall perform improvements to the Demised Premises (as reduced hereby) on the terms and subject to the conditions set forth in
<U>
	Exhibit&nbsp;B
</U>
	.&#160; Lessor is under no obligation to make any Alterations in or to the Demised Premises (as reduced hereby) or the Building; provided, however, that Lessor agrees to construct a multi-tenant elevator lobby and (subject to

	Exhibit&nbsp;B
</U>
	) common corridor on the seventh (7

	th
</FONT>

<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	) floor of the Building as of the date of this Lease (&#147;
<B>
	Lessor&#146;s Work
</B>
	&#148;).&#160; Lessor shall promptly commence Lessor&#146;s Work after Lessee&#146;s Plans (as defined in
<U>
	Exhibit&nbsp;B
</U>
	) with respect to the Re-Included Space are developed to a degree that permits Lessor to determine whether or not Lessor&#146;s Work will include non-cosmetic Alterations, and thereafter diligently pursue the same to completion.&#160; Lessor and Lessee shall reasonably cooperate with each other to avoid interference if Lessor&#146;s

	Work and the Leasehold Improvements are being performed simultaneously.&#160; If Lessor&#146;s Work includes non-cosmetic Alterations, and Lessor&#146;s failure to perform the same prevents Lessee from lawfully reoccupying the portion of the Demised Premises (as reduced hereby) located on the seventh (7

</B>

</B>

</B>
	&#148; shall mean Fifteen Thousand Dollars ($15,000.00) for each of the first three (3)&nbsp;such extensions and Twenty Thousand Dollars ($20,000.00) for each of the remaining three (3)&nbsp;extensions.&#160; For the avoidance of doubt, such Extension Payments shall not be credited against any of Lessee&#146;s other obligations under the Lease, as amended hereby.&#160; If Lessee timely delivers the Lessee Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Hold Space Option Notice, Lessor shall deliver the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Hold Space to Lessee not later than four (4)&nbsp;months following the date of Lessee&#146;s Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Hold Space Option Notice (the &#147;
<B>
	Anticipated Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Hold Space Delivery Date
</B>
	&#148;).&#160; Lessee may not lease less than all of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Hold Space designated by Lessor.&#160; Lessee shall have no right to rescind its election to lease the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Hold Space.&#160; Prior to December&nbsp;31, 2015, Lessor shall have no right to lease or license the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Hold Space to a third party, but such space may be utilized by Lessor or its affiliate or parent entities for internal use.

<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	) floor with a demising wall constructed, but Lessor shall have no obligation to perform any further work with respect to the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space or the delivery thereof.&#160; Such demising wall shall be constructed in a manner in compliance with applicable laws and consistent with Building standard finishes.&#160; Without limiting the generality of the effect of the foregoing, the corridor side of any such demising wall shall be consistent with Lessor&#146;s Work.&#160; Subject to the foregoing, Lessee may exercise the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space Expansion Option by giving written notice to Lessor no later than October&nbsp;31, 2018 (&#147;

	(B)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

	Lessee&#146;s exercise of its Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space Option shall be subject to the following conditions at the time of such exercise:&#160; (i)&nbsp;the Lease (as amended hereby) is in full force and effect; (ii)&nbsp;no default by Lessee then exists beyond any applicable notice and cure period; (iii)&nbsp;Lessee has timely exercised the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space Option, with time being of the essence; (iv)&nbsp;the Lease (as amended hereby) had not been assigned in a transaction requiring Lessor&#146;s consent pursuant to Section&nbsp;11 of the Original Lease (as amended and restated by Section&nbsp;12 of Addendum No.&nbsp;4) (Lessor acknowledging that Lessor&#146;s consent is not required for an assignment of the Lease or sublet of the Demised Premises to any subsidiary, affiliate or successor (as those terms are defined in Section&nbsp;11 of the Original Lease)); (v)&nbsp;Lessee is occupying for the conduct of Lessee&#146;s business therein more than seventy percent (70%) of the rentable area of the Demised Premises; and (vi)&nbsp;Lessee shall not have exercised the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Hold Space Option.&#160; Except as provided below, if Lessee exercises its Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space Option, Lessee may not thereafter revoke such exercise.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(C)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

	The annual rate for Monthly Rent payable for the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

<A NAME="eolPage12"></A>

<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	shall be the annual Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Rate for the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space as of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Commencement Date (the &#147;
<B>
	Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Calculation Date
</B>
	&#148;), with such Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Rate being escalated annually on each anniversary of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Calculation Date by the market escalation rate that shall be determined as part of the determination of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Rate.&#160; The &#147;
<B>
	Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Rate
</B>
	&#148; shall mean the Market Base Rent (as defined in Section&nbsp;8 of the Original Lease).&#160; Subject to the provisions of this Section, the calculation of Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Rate shall take into account all relevant factors.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(D)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Procedure for Determining Monthly Rent.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(1)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	If Lessee exercises its right to lease the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space, Lessor shall advise Lessee (the &#147;
<B>
	Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Rent Notice
</B>
	&#148;) of Lessor&#146;s determination of Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Rate on or before November&nbsp;10, 2018.&#160; If Lessee does not accept Lessor&#146;s determination of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Rate, the parties shall meet and seek in good faith to reach agreement on the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Rate during the thirty (30) day period that begins when Lessor receives Lessee&#146;s Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Notice (the &#147;
<B>
	Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Negotiation Period
</B>
	&#148;).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(2)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	If Lessor and Lessee do not agree upon the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Rate in writing within the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Negotiation Period, the provisions of Section&nbsp;9(D)(2)&nbsp;of Addendum No.&nbsp;4 shall govern the determination of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Rate, except that all references in such Section&nbsp;9(D)(2)&nbsp;to:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	the &#147;Extension Rate&#148; shall mean the &#147;Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Rate&#148;;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	the &#147;Extension Negotiation Period&#148; shall mean the &#147;Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Negotiation Period&#148;; and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	the &#147;Extension Rent Notice&#148; shall mean the &#147;Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Rent Notice.&#148;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	If the Monthly Rent payable for the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space is not determined prior to the day on which Lessee commences to lease the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space, Lessee shall pay Monthly Rent for the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space in an amount equal to the rentable square foot rate then payable for the then current Demised Premises (the &#147;
<B>
	Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Interim Rent
</B>
	&#148;).&#160; Upon final determination of the Monthly Rent for the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space, Lessee shall commence paying such Monthly Rent as so determined, and within ten (10)&nbsp;days after such determination Lessee shall pay any deficiency in prior payments of Monthly Rent or, if the Monthly Rent as so determined shall be less than the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Interim Rent, Lessee shall be entitled to a credit against the next succeeding installments of Monthly Rent in an amount equal to the difference between each installment of Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Interim Rent and the Monthly Rent as so determined which should have been paid for such installment until the total amount of the over payment has been recouped.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(E)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Except to the extent expressly set forth in this Section&nbsp;to the contrary, if Lessee elects to lease the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space, such space shall become subject to the Lease (as amended hereby) upon the same terms and conditions as are then applicable to the then current Demised Premises. The foregoing notwithstanding, any tenant improvement allowances,

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

	free rent periods, moving allowances or other special concessions granted to Lessee with respect to the then current Demised Premises shall not apply to the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(F)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	If Lessee exercises its right to lease the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space, (1)&nbsp;the term of Lessee&#146;s lease of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space shall: (a)&nbsp;commence upon the date (the &#147;
<B>
	Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space Commencement Date
</B>
	&#148;) Lessor tenders possession of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space in the condition required under Section&nbsp;8(A)&nbsp;above, and (b)&nbsp;expire upon the expiration of the Lease Term, including any further extensions thereof, and (2)&nbsp;Lessee&#146;s obligation to pay Monthly Rent for the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space shall commence on the earlier of (a)&nbsp;the date that is ninety (90) days following the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space Commencement Date and (b)&nbsp;the date upon which Lessee commences occupancy of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space for its actual conduct of business.&#160; Provided Lessor has complied with the terms of the following sentence, Lessor will have no liability to Lessee if Lessor does not deliver the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space to Lessee on the date originally contemplated by Lessor for any causes beyond the reasonable control of Lessor.&#160; Lessor will promptly commence and diligently pursue obtaining possession of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space (including, if necessary, by initiating legal proceedings) so that Lessor can tender the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space to Lessee; provided, however, that the following shall be Lessee&#146;s sole remedies if Lessor complied with the foregoing sentence but failed timely to deliver the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space:&#160; (x)&nbsp;if Lessor has not tendered possession of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space to Lessee within ninety (90) days after the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space Delivery Date (which date shall not be extended by Force Majeure), then Lessee shall receive an abatement of Monthly Rent for the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space and Lessee&#146;s proportionate share of Operating Costs, Operating Expenses and Real Estate Taxes for the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space equal to one-half (&#189;) day for each day of such delay from and after the ninety-first (91
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	st
</FONT>
	) day after the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space Delivery Date; provided, however, that (i)&nbsp;such abatement shall not exceed, in the aggregate, ninety (90) days of Monthly Rent for the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space and Lessee&#146;s proportionate share of Operating Costs, Operating Expenses and Real Estate Taxes for the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space (i.e., such abatement shall cease to accrue after the two hundred seventieth (270
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	) day after the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space Delivery Date) and (ii)&nbsp;for the avoidance of doubt, such abatement shall not be applicable if Lessee terminates its election to lease the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space pursuant to clause (y)&nbsp;below; and (y)&nbsp;if Lessor has not tendered possession of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space to Lessee within one hundred eighty (180) days after the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space Delivery Date (which date shall not be extended by Force Majeure), Lessee shall have the right to terminate its election to lease the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space by notifying Lessor in writing within thirty (30) days after the expiration of said one hundred eighty (180) day period, in which event Lessee&#146;s rights under this Section&nbsp;8 shall lapse.&#160; Lessor shall have no obligation to make any payment to the occupant or to give any other concession to such occupant in order to induce such occupant to vacate and surrender possession of any Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space.
</P>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

	Except to the extent expressly set forth in the Lease (as amended hereby) to the contrary, upon Lessee&#146;s leasing of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space, the rentable area of the Demised Premises and term &#147;Demised Premises&#148; shall be deemed amended to include the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space and Lessee&#146;s proportionate share and all other computations made under the Lease (as amended hereby) based upon or affected by the rentable area of the Demised Premises shall be recomputed to include the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space; provided

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	that, the computation of the square footage of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space shall be based on BOMA.

	(H)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

	From and after the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space Commencement Date, Lessee shall be provided with (i)&nbsp;additional parking permits (at the prevailing market rate for such permits) in the ratio of one (1)&nbsp;contract for every one thousand five hundred (1,500) square feet of rentable area in the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space (BOMA measured), with such entitlement to parking permits being otherwise subject to Section&nbsp;12 of this Addendum No.&nbsp;5, and (ii)&nbsp;its pro rata share of additional directory strips in the building directory.

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

	Notwithstanding the foregoing to the contrary, if Lessee extends the Lessee Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Hold Space Option Notice Deadline but does not exercise the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Hold Space Option, then the dates set forth in Sections 9(A)&nbsp;and 9(D)(1)&nbsp;shall be extended for the same number of months as the Lessee Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Hold Space Option Notice Deadline is extended.

</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

<U>

</U>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">

	(A)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(1)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Subject to the provisions of this Section&nbsp;10, if, during the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Extension Term and, if exercised, the Second Extension Term (but not any further extensions of the Lease Term), any portion of the Additional Give-Back Premises becomes available for lease from Lessor (or Lessor reasonably anticipates that such space will become available for lease from Lessor) (the &#147;
<B>
	Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space
</B>
	&#148;), Lessor shall so notify Lessee (the &#147;
<B>
	Lessor&#146;s Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Notice
</B>
	&#148;) of the anticipated availability date (the &#147;
<B>
	Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Delivery Date
</B>
	&#148;) and the location of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space, and Lessee shall have the right to lease all (but not less than all) of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space (the &#147;
<B>
	Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Right of Opportunity
</B>
	&#148;) by delivering Lessee&#146;s notice of such election to Lessor (&#147;
<B>
	Lessee&#146;s Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Notice
</B>
	&#148;) within ten (10)&nbsp;business days after Lessor gives Lessor&#146;s Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Notice to Lessee.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(2)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Any provision of the Lease (as amended hereby) to the contrary notwithstanding, Lessee&#146;s Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Right of Opportunity shall be subject to the following:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Lessee&#146;s Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Right of Opportunity shall not apply to any Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space until Lessor has entered into a lease with a third-party tenant for such Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space containing such terms as Lessor deems acceptable in Lessor&#146;s sole discretion (including, without limitation, any fixed expansion or extension rights that Lessor might grant such tenant(s)&nbsp;for such Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space) with a third-party tenant and the term of such lease has expired with respect to such Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space (including, without limitation, the expiration of any lease term extension period(s)) or otherwise been terminated.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	If Lessee notifies Lessor that Lessee elects not to lease an Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space or if Lessee fails to timely deliver Lessee&#146;s Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Notice to Lessor with respect thereto, Lessee&#146;s Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Right of Opportunity shall not apply to such Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space until Lessor has thereafter entered into a lease for such Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space with a third-party tenant under one or more leases
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	containing such terms as Lessor deems acceptable in Lessor&#146;s sole discretion (including, without limitation, any right of opportunity or other expansion rights that Lessor might grant such tenant(s)&nbsp;for such Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space) and Lessor&#146;s Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Right of Opportunity shall not apply to such space until the term of such lease has expired with respect to such Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space (including, without limitation, the expiration of any lease term extension period(s)) or otherwise been terminated.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	The fixed expansion or extension rights of the third party tenant(s)&nbsp;taking all or any portion of the Additional Give-Back Premises pursuant to the initial lease-up following Lessee&#146;s surrender of the Additional Give-Back Premises hereunder (a &#147;
<B>
	Lease-Up Lessee&#146;s Rights
</B>
	&#148;).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(B)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Conditions to Exercise.&#160; Lessee&#146;s exercise of its Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Right of Opportunity shall be subject to the following conditions at the time of such exercise:&#160; (i)&nbsp;the Lease (as amended hereby) is in full force and effect; (ii)&nbsp;no default by Lessee then exists beyond any applicable notice and cure period; (iii)&nbsp;Lessee has timely exercised the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Right of Opportunity, with time being of the essence; (iv)&nbsp;the Lease (as amended hereby) had not been assigned in a transaction requiring Lessor&#146;s consent pursuant to Section&nbsp;11 of the Original Lease (as amended and restated by Section&nbsp;12 of Addendum No.&nbsp;4) (Lessor acknowledging that Lessor&#146;s consent is not required for an assignment of the Lease or sublet of the Demised Premises to any subsidiary, affiliate or successor (as those terms are defined in Section&nbsp;11 of the Original Lease)); (v)&nbsp;Lessee is occupying for the conduct of Lessee&#146;s business therein more than seventy percent (70%) of the rentable area of the Demised Premises; and (vi)&nbsp;Lessee shall not have exercised the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Hold Space Option.&#160; Except as provided herein, if Lessee exercises its Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Right of Opportunity, Lessee may not thereafter revoke such exercise.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(C)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Condition of Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space.&#160; Lessee shall take the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space in &#147;as is&#148; condition, except, however, base Building systems serving the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space shall be in good working order.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(D)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space Rent.&#160; The annual rate for Monthly Rent payable for an applicable Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space shall be the annual Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Rate for the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space as of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Commencement Date (the &#147;
<B>
	Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Calculation Date
</B>
	&#148;), with such Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Rate being escalated annually on each anniversary of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Calculation Date by the market escalation rate that shall be determined as part of the determination of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Rate.&#160; The &#147;
<B>
	Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Rate
</B>
	&#148; shall mean the Market Base Rent (as defined in Section&nbsp;8 of the Original Lease).&#160; Subject to the provisions of this Section, the calculation of Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Rate shall take into account all relevant factors.&#160; If the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Rate includes any out-of-pocket monetary concession (such as a tenant improvement allowance) to be provided by Lessor, Lessor shall have the option to either directly provide such monetary concession or indirectly provide such monetary concession by equitably reducing the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Rate by the economic value of such concession over the then remaining Lease Term.
</P>

	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">

</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Lessor shall advise Lessee (the &#147;
<B>
	Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Rent Notice
</B>
	&#148;) of Lessor&#146;s determination of Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Rate within ten (10)&nbsp;days after receiving Lessee&#146;s Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Notice.&#160; If Lessee does not accept Lessor&#146;s determination of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Rate, the parties shall meet and seek in good faith to reach agreement on the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Rate during the thirty (30) day period that begins when Lessor receives Lessee&#146;s Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Notice (the &#147;
<B>
	Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Negotiation Period
</B>
	&#148;).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(2)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	If Lessor and Lessee do not agree upon the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Rate in writing within the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Negotiation Period, the provisions of Section&nbsp;9(D)(2)&nbsp;of Addendum No.&nbsp;4 shall govern the determination of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Rate, except that all references in such Section&nbsp;9(D)(2)&nbsp;to:

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">

	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	If the Monthly Rent payable for an Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space is not determined prior to the day on which Lessee commences to lease the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space, Lessee shall pay Monthly Rent for the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space in an amount equal to the rentable square foot rate then payable for the then current Demised Premises (the &#147;
<B>
	Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Interim Rent
</B>
	&#148;).&#160; Upon final determination of the Monthly Rent for the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space, Lessee shall commence paying such Monthly Rent as so determined, and within ten (10)&nbsp;days after such determination Lessee shall pay any deficiency in prior payments of Monthly Rent or, if the Monthly Rent as so determined shall be less than the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Interim Rent, Lessee shall be entitled to a credit against the next succeeding installments of Monthly Rent in an amount equal to the difference between each installment of Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Interim Rent and the Monthly Rent as so determined which should have been paid for such installment until the total amount of the over payment has been recouped.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">

	(F)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Except to the extent expressly set forth in this Section&nbsp;to the contrary, if Lessee elects to lease Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space, such space shall become subject to the Lease (as amended hereby) upon the same terms and conditions as are then applicable to the then current Demised Premises. The foregoing notwithstanding, any tenant improvement allowances, free rent periods, moving allowances or other special concessions granted to Lessee with respect to the then current Demised Premises shall not apply to the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">

	(G)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	If Lessee exercises its right to lease Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space, the term of Lessee&#146;s lease of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space shall: (a)&nbsp;commence upon the date (the &#147;
<B>
	Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space Commencement Date
</B>
	&#148;) that is the later of:&#160; (i)&nbsp;the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Delivery Date, or (ii)&nbsp;the date Lessor tenders possession of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space in the condition required under Section&nbsp;8(C)&nbsp;above, and (b)&nbsp;expire upon the expiration of the Lease Term, including any further extensions thereof (or, if Lessee&#146;s rights
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	under Section&nbsp;8 above remain unexercised but available, and Lessor notifies Lessee in the Lessor&#146;s Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Notice that such Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space constitutes Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space, expire on the day before the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 Option Space Commencement Date).&#160; Provided Lessor has complied with the terms of the following sentence, Lessor will have no liability to Lessee if Lessor does not deliver the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space to Lessee on the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Delivery Date for any causes beyond the reasonable control of Lessor.&#160; Lessor will promptly commence and diligently pursue obtaining possession of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space (including, if necessary, by initiating legal proceedings) so that Lessor can tender the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space to Lessee; provided, however, that the following shall be Lessee&#146;s sole remedies if Lessor complied with the foregoing sentence but failed timely to deliver the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space:&#160; (x)&nbsp;if Lessor has not tendered possession of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space to Lessee within ninety (90) days after the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Delivery Date (which date shall not be extended by Force Majeure), then Lessee shall receive an abatement of Monthly Rent for the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space and Lessee&#146;s proportionate share of Operating Costs, Operating Expenses and Real Estate Taxes for the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space equal to one-half (&#189;) day for each day of such delay from and after the ninety-first (91
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	st
</FONT>
	) day after the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Delivery Date; provided, however, that (i)&nbsp;such abatement shall not exceed, in the aggregate, ninety (90) days of Monthly Rent for the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space and Lessee&#146;s proportionate share of Operating Costs, Operating Expenses and Real Estate Taxes for the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space (i.e., such abatement shall cease to accrue after the two hundred seventieth (270
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	) day after the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Delivery Date) and (ii)&nbsp;for the avoidance of doubt, such abatement shall not be applicable if Lessee terminates its election to lease the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space pursuant to clause (y)&nbsp;below; and (y)&nbsp;if Lessor has not tendered possession of the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space to Lessee within one hundred eighty (180) days after the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Delivery Date (which date shall not be extended by Force Majeure), Lessee shall have the right to terminate its election to lease the Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space by notifying Lessor in writing within thirty (30) days after the expiration of said one hundred eighty (180) day period, in which event Lessee&#146;s rights under this Section&nbsp;9 shall lapse.&#160; Lessor shall have no obligation to make any payment to the occupant or to give any other concession to such occupant in order to induce such occupant to vacate and surrender possession of any Addendum No.&nbsp;5 ROFO Space.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">

	(H)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

<B>
	Lender Approval
</B>
	&#148;).&#160; The terms and conditions of this Addendum No.&nbsp;5 shall not be effective until the Effective Date.&#160; The term &#147;
<B>
	Effective Date
</B>
	&#148; shall mean the later to occur of the following dates:&#160; (a)&nbsp;the date this Addendum No.&nbsp;5 is fully executed, and (b)&nbsp;the date upon which Lessor advises Lessee in writing that Lender Approval has been received (the &#147;
<B>
	Lender Approval Notification Date
</B>
	&#148;).&#160; Lessor shall use commercially reasonable, good faith, diligent efforts to obtain Lender Approval as soon as is reasonably possible following the full execution of this Addendum No.&nbsp;5.&#160; If the Lender Approval Notification Date does not occur within forty (40) days following the date on which this Addendum No.&nbsp;5 has been fully executed by Lessor and Lessee, then Lessee shall have the right to cancel this Addendum No.&nbsp;5 upon five (5)&nbsp;days&#146; prior written notice to Lessor, such notice to be given, if at all, prior to the Lender Approval Notification Date.&#160; If the Lender Approval Notification Date does not occur within fifty-five (55) days following the date on which this Addendum No.&nbsp;5 has been fully executed by Lessor and Lessee, then, provided Lessor has used its commercially reasonable good faith diligent efforts to obtain Lender Approval as required above, Lessor shall have the right to cancel this Addendum No.&nbsp;5 upon five (5)&nbsp;days&#146; prior written notice to Lessee, such notice to be given, if at all, prior to the Lender Approval Notification Date.&#160; If this Addendum No.&nbsp;5 is cancelled by Lessor or Lessee as aforesaid, (i)&nbsp;this Addendum No.&nbsp;5 shall be null and void as if the same had never been executed by Lessor and Lessee, (ii)&nbsp;the Lease as un-amended by this Addendum No.&nbsp;5 shall remain in full force and effect, and (iii)&nbsp;neither party hereto shall have any rights against or obligations to the other under this Addendum No.&nbsp;5.

<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	EXHIBIT&nbsp;B
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	WORK AGREEMENT
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	This Work Agreement is a part of Addendum No.&nbsp;5. In the event of any conflict between the terms of this Work Agreement and the terms of the Lease (as amended by Addendum No.&nbsp;5), the terms of this Work Agreement shall control.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<U>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Article&nbsp;1 - Definitions
</FONT>
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Definitions
</U>
	.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.1
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Base Building Plans
</B>
	&#148; means the base building plans and specifications for the Building.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.2
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Base Building Systems
</B>
	&#148; means the structural components of the Building and the mechanical, electrical, plumbing, sanitary, sprinkler, heating, ventilation and air conditioning, security, life-safety and other service systems or facilities of the Building up to the point of connection for localized distribution to the Demised Premises and the mechanical, electrical, plumbing, heating, ventilation and air conditioning, elevators and other service systems or facilities servicing the common areas of the Building.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.3
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Change Order
</B>
	&#148; means any change in any of Lessee&#146;s Plans after Lessor has approved any such plan and/or any change in the work or materials to be included in the Leasehold Improvements.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.4
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Comparable Building
</B>
	&#148; means first-class office buildings of comparable age and size in the central business district of the District of Columbia.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.5
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Contractor
</B>
	&#148; means the general contractor selected by Lessee in accordance with the terms of this Work Agreement to construct and install the Leasehold Improvements.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.6
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Construction Costs
</B>
	&#148; means all costs in the permitting, demolition, construction and installation of the Leasehold Improvements and acquiring the materials for the Leasehold Improvements.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.7
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Effective Date
</B>
	&#148; has the meaning given such term in Addendum No.&nbsp;5.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.8
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Engineers
</B>
	&#148; means the mechanical, electrical, plumbing and structural and engineers and other licensed third-parties selected by Lessee to assist in the preparation of Lessee&#146;s Plans.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.9
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Essential Subs
</B>
	&#148; means those subcontractors to be specifically designated by Lessor acting reasonably for purposes of working on the Building mechanical, energy management, structural, exterior windows (including window removal and reinstallation for hoisting purposes), roof (excluding HVAC), sprinkler and fire and life safety systems.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<A NAME="eolPage25"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.10
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Final Space Plan
</B>
	&#148; means a detailed space plan for the Leasehold Improvements prepared by Lessee&#146;s Architect, which space plan shall be substantially in conformance with the Preliminary Plan approved by Lessor and any updates or changes thereto approved by Lessor and shall contain the information and otherwise comply with the requirements set forth on Annex 2 attached hereto.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.11
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Improvement Costs
</B>
	&#148; means, collectively, (i)&nbsp;the Soft Costs; (ii)&nbsp;the Construction Costs; and (iii)&nbsp;Lessor&#146;s Fee.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.12
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Leasehold Improvements
</B>
	&#148; means the improvements set forth in Lessee&#146;s Plans as approved by Lessor in accordance with the terms of this Work Agreement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.13
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Lessee&#146;s Architect
</B>
	&#148; means the architect engaged by Lessee to design the Leasehold Improvements and prepare Lessee&#146;s Plans.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.14
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Lessee&#146;s Contractors
</B>
	&#148; means Contractor and all subcontractors and subsubcontractors (including the Essential Subs) who will work on the Leasehold Improvements.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.15
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Lessee&#146;s Equipment
</B>
	&#148; means any telephone, telephone switching, telephone and data cabling, furniture, computers, servers, Lessee&#146;s trade fixtures and other personal property to be installed by or on behalf of Lessee in the Demised Premises.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.16
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

<A NAME="eolPage27"></A>

<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	reoccupancy by Lessee resulting therefrom including, without limitation, costs or expenses relating to (i)&nbsp;any additional architectural or engineering services and related design expenses; (ii)&nbsp;any reasonable architectural or engineering costs incurred by Lessor in connection with its review of such requested change; (iii)&nbsp;any changes to materials in process of fabrication; (iv)&nbsp;cancellation or modification of supply or fabricating contracts; (v)&nbsp;removal or alteration of work or plans completed or in process; or (vi)&nbsp;delay claims made by Contractor.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	No changes shall be made to any of Lessee&#146;s Plans and no Change Orders shall be implemented without the prior written approval of Lessor, which approval shall not be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed (but which shall be subject to the Alterations limitations set forth in the Lease). All Change Orders shall be in writing and shall be on such AIA form as is required by Lessor and/or Contractor. Lessee shall evidence in writing its approval of any Change Order prior to requesting Lessor&#146;s approval of same.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	2.6
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

</U>
	.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Lessee shall cause (i)&nbsp;Lessee&#146;s Plans to comply with all Applicable Laws; (ii)&nbsp;Lessee&#146;s Plans to be prepared by Lessee&#146;s Architect and the Engineers in accordance with the terms of this Work Agreement and in conformity with the Base Building Plans and the base Building systems (including, without limitation, the base Building HVAC, mechanical, electrical, plumbing and life safety systems); (iii)&nbsp;the Plans and Specifications to be sufficient to enable Contractor (with respect to the Plans and Specifications) to obtain all necessary Permits; and (iv)&nbsp;the Plans and Specifications to be prepared using the AutoCAD Computer Assisted Drafting and Design System format. Lessee shall cause Lessee&#146;s Plans not to include any Leasehold Improvements that will or that reasonably might be anticipated to (1)&nbsp;interfere with the normal operation of the Building, Building operations, or the Base Building Systems; (2)&nbsp;materially increase maintenance or utility charges for operating the Building in excess of the standard requirements for Comparable Buildings, or (3)&nbsp;affect the exterior or structure of the Building. Lessee shall cause Lessee&#146;s Plans to include as part of the Leasehold Improvements the construction of a Building standard demising wall to separate the Additional Give-Back Premises from the balance of the Demised Premises located on the seventh (7
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	) floor of the Building.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Any provision of this Work Agreement or the Lease (as amended by Addendum No.&nbsp;5) to the contrary notwithstanding, Lessor&#146;s approval of the Plans and Specifications shall not constitute an assurance by Lessor that the Plans and Specifications satisfy any Applicable Laws or are sufficient to enable the Contractor to obtain a building permit for the undertaking of the Leasehold Improvements. If Lessor notifies Lessee at any time that the Plans and Specifications must be revised due to their failure to comply with the terms of this Work Agreement, such revisions shall be made at Lessee&#146;s expense and any delay arising in connection therewith shall constitute a Lessee delay and shall not give rise to any claim or cause of action against Lessor.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Prior to making or installing any of the Leasehold Improvements, Lessee shall perform a field verification to independently determine the existing conditions, specifications and dimensions of the Demised Premises and any variances from the Base Building Plans.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

	Lessee has appointed Lessee&#146;s Representative for purposes of granting any consents or approvals by Lessee under this Work Agreement and for authorizing and executing any and all Change Orders or other documents in connection with this Work Agreement and Lessor shall have the right to rely on Lessee&#146;s Representative&#146;s consent, approval, authorization or execution as aforesaid.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(e)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Lessor has appointed Lessor&#146;s Representative for purposes of granting any consents or approvals by Lessor under this Work Agreement and for authorizing and executing any and all Change Orders or other documents in connection with this Work Agreement and Lessee shall have the right to rely on Lessor&#146;s Representative&#146;s consent, approval, authorization or execution as aforesaid.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">

</FONT>

</FONT>
	Lessee shall reimburse Lessor for all reasonable out-of-pocket costs incurred by Lessor in reviewing any proposed Lessee Plans and Change Orders within thirty (30) days after Lessee&#146;s receipt of an invoice therefor.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<U>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Article&nbsp;3 &#151; Construction
</FONT>
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	3.1
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Lessor Improvements
</U>
	. Except as might be expressly set forth in Addendum No.&nbsp;5 to the contrary, Lessor has no obligation to do any other work or pay any amounts with respect to the Demised Premises.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	3.2
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Leasehold Improvements
</U>
	. Lessee shall, at Lessee&#146;s expense, Substantially Complete the Leasehold Improvements in a good and workmanlike manner and in accordance with the terms of this Work Agreement not later than on October&nbsp;31, 2015. Except to the extent that the Plans and Specifications provide otherwise, Lessee will cause the Leasehold Improvements to be constructed of new materials commensurate with the level of improvements for a typical first-class tenant in Comparable Buildings.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	3.3
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	General Contractor
</U>
	.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Lessor has previously approved the contract and general contractor (Rand Construction) relating to the construction of the Leasehold Improvements.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	The Contractor shall be responsible for all required construction, management and supervision of the Lessee Improvement work.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	3.4
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Subcontractors
</U>
	. Lessor shall have the right to approve Lessee&#146;s subcontractors, such approval not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	3.5
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Certain Essential Work
</U>
	.&#160; All Lessee Improvement connections or tie-ins to the base Building energy management, sprinkler and fire and life safety systems shall be performed at Lessee&#146;s expense by the applicable Essential Sub. All Lessee Improvement work relating to the Building exterior walls and windows (including window removal and reinstallation for hoisting purposes), and the roof (excluding HVAC), shall be performed at Lessee&#146;s expense by the applicable Essential Sub.
</P>

</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

	3.8
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

<U>
	Lessee&#146;s Equipment
</U>
	.&#160; Lessee, at Lessee&#146;s expense, shall be responsible for ordering and for the delivery and installation of Lessee&#146;s Equipment.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">

	3.9
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
	Post Construction Activities
</U>
	.&#160; Prior to Lessee&#146;s use or reoccupancy of the Demised Premises or any portion thereof and Lessor&#146;s disbursement of any portion of the Retainage, Lessee shall, at Lessee&#146;s expense, deliver to Lessor all certifications and approvals with respect to the Leasehold Improvements that may be required from any governmental authority and/or any board or fire underwriters or similar body for the use and/or occupancy of the Demised Premises; and certificates of insurance evidencing all insurance coverage required under the Lease and this Work Agreement.
</P>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">

	3.10
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

<U>
	General Construction Provisions
</U>
	.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Any damage caused by Lessee&#146;s Contractors to any portion of the Building or to any property of Lessor or other tenants shall be repaired forthwith after written notice from Lessor to its condition prior to such damage by Lessee at Lessee&#146;s expense.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Lessee and Lessee&#146;s Contractors shall access the Demised Premises via the Building freight elevator, work in harmony and not interfere with the performance of other work in the Building.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	If at any time such entry shall cause, or in Lessor&#146;s reasonable judgment threaten to cause, such disharmony or interference, Lessor may terminate such permission upon 24 hours&#146; notice to Lessee, and thereupon, Lessee or its employees, agents, contractors, and suppliers causing such disharmony or interference shall immediately withdraw from the Demised Premises and the Building until Lessor reasonably determines such disturbance no longer exists.

<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
